&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary / Objective&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key member of the global eCommerce organization, the Digital Shelf SEO &amp;amp; GEO Manager is the enterprise leader responsible for leading MadeGood brand discovery and conversion across search engines, LLM’s, &amp;amp; retailer digital shelf environments.&amp;nbsp; This role partners closely with MarTech, IT, brand, &amp;amp; multiple agency teams to ensure item attributes are accurate, PDP’s are compliant, content is compelling, and continuous optimization efforts are in place.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to driving the PDP content agenda on Retailer.com, this individual will also lead agentic commerce capability development to improve brand discovery and consideration at scale.&amp;nbsp; This includes (but is not limited to) ensuring structured content, metadata, and workflows enable scalable optimization across product listing pages within eCommerce platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, the Digital Shelf SEO &amp;amp; GEO Manager will function as the digital shelf SME leading diagnostic reporting &amp;amp; competitive intelligence via Profitero, Stackline, and various other reporting tools.&amp;nbsp; They will play a vital role in delivering executive-level performance insights, along with analytics support behind robust PDP test &amp;amp; learn plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-impact role in a high-growth business with influence on both near-term performance and long-term channel evolution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PDP Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead product content publishing and syndication effort across retailer websites including Amazon, Walmart, Costco, Sam’s Target, Kroger, Instacart, Albertsons, Thrive, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate product listings, images, enhanced content, attributes, R&amp;amp;R’s, &amp;amp; nutritional information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive structured content standards (metadata, taxonomy, schema) to enable scalable content reuse, consistency, and optimization across DAM, PIM, and CMS ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content Optimization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage digital shelf analytics and competitive audits to inform SEO / GEO roadmap incl. product titles, descriptions, feature bullets, keywords.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development and execution of A+ content and onsite brand shops in partnership with commerce marketing manager and brand teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive digital shelf &amp;amp; GEO performance through analytics, competitive benchmarking, and rapid testing of evolving SEO, GEO, and Agentic capabilities.&lt;/li

